<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-174-610  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 174 610.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Feb 23 1990 n1371* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tridata, Mitem team to offer IBM 370 users application access fromMac. (Tri-Data Systems Inc.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tri-Data (product introduction)Mitem Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)MitemView (Program development software) (product introduction)IBM 370 (Mainframe computer) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMicro-Mainframe CommunicationProgram Development ToolsSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>TRIDATA, MITEM TEAM TO OFFER IBM 370 USERSandM;APPLICATION ACCESS FROM MACandM;Tri-Data Systems Inc, Santa Clara, California and Mitem Corp have introducedMitemView support for Netway.andP;  This enables the creation of intelligentgraphical user interfaces to IBM mainframe applications on Apple Computer IncMacintosh computers without the need to make any modification to the hostcode, via a local area network-based SNA gateway.andP;  MitemView uses Tri-Data's3270 Application Program Interface to support multiple host sessions andsimultaneous communication with multiple mainframes.andP;  It provides a set ofcommunications tools to develop applications using the HyperCard program,designed to simplify access and retrieval from host-based applications.andO;MitemView is a Macintosh software development tool for creating point andclick graphical user interfaces to mainframe applications without host codemodification.andP;  Mitem says that since it is based on Hypercard, it is able totake a loosely coupled approach to graphical front-ends.andP;  Tri-Data's Netwayacts as a 3174 cluster controller on an SNA network and replaces the need fora co-ax or Token-Ring card in each Macintosh.andP;  Netway's applications programinterface functions provide a series of procedural calls for establishing3270 sessions, sending and receiving host screens, manipulating screen data,and terminating 3270 host sessions.andP;  Netway 1000, which supports 16simultaneous sessions, costs $4,000.andP;  Netway 2000 supports 64 simultaneoussessions and costs $10,000.andP;  The MitemView developer's toolkit is $1,000, andthe personality module that is required by MitemView to drive Netway costs$500, and includes the applications program interface.andO;</TEXT></DOC>